                           <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B00KY4S388?tag=skymaxx0e-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"sponsored noopener noreferrer\">\n                            <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"/images/img-828.jpg\" alt=\"Outland Living Portable Propane Fire Pit, 19-inch, 58,000 BTU wit...\">\n                        </a>\n                                </div>\n            <div class=\"hostinger-affiliate-block-list-simple__product-data\">\n                <div class=\"hostinger-affiliate-block-list-simple__product-info\">\n                                            <div class=\"hostinger-affiliate-block-list-simple__bestseller-label\">\n                                                        Bestseller #4                        </div>\n                                            <div class=\"hostinger-affiliate-block-list-simple__product-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B00KY4S388?tag=skymaxx0e-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"sponsored noopener noreferrer\">\n                            <h3>\n                                Outland Living Portable Propane Fire Pit, 19-inch, 58,000 BTU wit&#8230;                            </h3>\n                        </a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"hostinger-affiliate-block-list-simple__product-pricing\">\n                                                    <div class=\"hostinger-affiliate-block-list-simple__product-price\">\n                                $149.99                            </div>\n                                                </div>\n                </div>\n                <div class=\"hostinger-affiliate-block-list-simple__product-actions\">\n                    <div>\n                        <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B00KY4S388?tag=skymaxx0e-20\" class=\"hostinger-affiliate-block-list-simple__product-amazon-button\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"sponsored noopener noreferrer\">\n    Buy on Amazon</a>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n                <div class=\"hostinger-affiliate-block-list-simple\">\n            <div class=\"hostinger-affiliate-block-list-simple__image\">\n                                        <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0D95HGG98?tag=skymaxx0e-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"sponsored noopener noreferrer\">\n                            <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"/images/img-830.jpg\" alt=\"VEVOR 28 inch Smokeless Fire Pit Stove Bonfire, Wood Burning Fire...\">\n                        </a>\n                                </div>\n            <div class=\"hostinger-affiliate-block-list-simple__product-data\">\n                <div class=\"hostinger-affiliate-block-list-simple__product-info\">\n                                            <div class=\"hostinger-affiliate-block-list-simple__bestseller-label\">\n                                                        Bestseller #5                        </div>\n                                            <div class=\"hostinger-affiliate-block-list-simple__product-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0D95HGG98?tag=skymaxx0e-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"sponsored noopener noreferrer\">\n                            <h3>\n                                VEVOR 28 inch Smokeless Fire Pit Stove Bonfire, Wood Burning Fire&#8230;                            </h3>\n                        </a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"hostinger-affiliate-block-list-simple__product-pricing\">\n                                                    <div class=\"hostinger-affiliate-block-list-simple__product-price\">\n                                $225.99                            </div>\n                                                </div>\n                </div>\n                <div class=\"hostinger-affiliate-block-list-simple__product-actions\">\n                    <div>\n                        <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0D95HGG98?tag=skymaxx0e-20\" class=\"hostinger-affiliate-block-list-simple__product-amazon-button\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"sponsored noopener noreferrer\">\n    Buy on Amazon</a>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        </div>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><br></p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Project Overview</h2>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>Difficulty Level:</strong> 7 / 10<br><strong>Estimated Cost:</strong> $200 – $400<br><strong>Build Time:</strong> 2–4 hours</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">This project is achievable for experienced DIYers and homeowners comfortable with basic tools.</p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Why Choose a Smokeless Fire Pit?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Smokeless fire pits are designed to burn wood more efficiently by re-burning smoke particles before they escape into the air.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Key Benefits</h3>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Significantly reduced smoke</li>\n\n\n\n<li>More efficient wood burning</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Cleaner air for guests sensitive to smoke</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Less lingering odor on clothes</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Better heat output with less fuel</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Instead of smoke drifting sideways, a smokeless fire pit pulls air from below and re-ignites smoke through <strong>secondary combustion</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Materials &amp; Tools Required</h2>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Before starting, gather everything you need to avoid interruptions.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.thespruce.com/thmb/Fd30u3ZLBWUYHuj5u-LKRI7CU7Y%3D/1500x0/filters%3Ano_upscale%28%29%3Amax_bytes%28150000%29%3Astrip_icc%28%29/How-to-build-a-firepit-4160705_final-9c93111ba91744b2a95941148bf1987f.png\" alt=\"Image\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"/images/img-832.jpg\" alt=\"Image\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://contentgrid.homedepot-static.com/hdus/en_US/DTCCOMNEW/Articles/how-to-build-a-diy-fire-pit-with-a-seating-area-image-23.jpg\" alt=\"Image\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Core Materials</h3>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Metal fire pit ring or steel insert</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Masonry pavers or fire-rated blocks</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Gravel or crushed stone</li>\n\n\n\n<li>High-heat spray paint</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Fire-resistant sealant (if required)</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Tools</h3>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Drill with metal drill bits</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Measuring tape and marker</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Level</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Shovel</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Safety gloves and glasses</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How to Build a DIY Smokeless Fire Pit (Step-by-Step)</h2>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Step 1: Choose and Mark the Location</h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Select a flat, open area away from trees, structures, or slopes. Mark a circular outline for your pit (approximately 60 inches in diameter).</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.belgard.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/fire-pit-patio-design-1-1.jpg\" alt=\"Image\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.hello-hayley.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/fire-pit-ideas-3-683x1024.jpg\" alt=\"Image\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Step 2: Drill Air Vent Holes in the Insert</h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Mark evenly spaced points around the metal fire pit ring. Drill holes approximately <strong>1–3 inches from the top</strong>, leaving about <strong>2 inches between holes</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://fixthisbuildthat.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/DIY-Smokeless-Fire-Pit-10.jpg\" alt=\"Image\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://starfiredirect.com/cdn/shop/articles/why-vent-fire-pits-blog-main-image_5bafed65-a94f-4f4d-9409-48a99f43b7aa.jpg?v=1761085100\" alt=\"Image\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">These holes allow heated air and smoke to re-ignite during secondary combustion.</p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Step 3: Enlarge and Smooth the Holes</h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Enlarge holes if needed and file sharp edges to prevent injury and improve airflow.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://static.wixstatic.com/media/9c5dcf_4a2bcb33a02848d5b0aa67cc7c9ee389~mv2.png/v1/fit/w_500%2Ch_500%2Cq_90/file.png\" alt=\"Image\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://starfiredirect.com/cdn/shop/articles/why-vent-fire-pits-blog-main-image_5bafed65-a94f-4f4d-9409-48a99f43b7aa.jpg?v=1761085100\" alt=\"Image\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Step 4: Prepare the Fire Pit Base</h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Remove turf and dig a shallow base about <strong>2 inches deep</strong>. Add gravel for drainage and level the surface carefully.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.jennasuedesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/IMG_8633-1.jpg\" alt=\"Image\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://thriftdiving.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Fire-Pit-In-Your-Backyard-Create-an-easy-fire-pit-in-just-a-couple-of-hours-with-this-fire-pit-kit-copy.jpg\" alt=\"Image\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Step 5: Establish the First Paver Tier</h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Place the metal insert at the center and build the first ring of pavers around it, leaving a <strong>2-inch gap</strong> between the insert and blocks.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Remove several blocks at the base on one side to allow fresh air intake.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://westerninterlock.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Tegula-Firepit-Cambridge-Blend-Charcoal-Roca-Rotundo-Cap-Portland-Oregon.jpg\" alt=\"Image\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://westerninterlock.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/how-to-build-circle-paver-patio-fire-pit-19.jpg\" alt=\"Image\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Step 6: Build Additional Paver Layers</h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Stack additional paver tiers, staggering joints for stability. Use masonry adhesive between layers.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://westerninterlock.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Tegula-Firepit-Cambridge-Blend-Charcoal-Roca-Rotundo-Cap-Portland-Oregon.jpg\" alt=\"Image\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.thegardenglove.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/How-to-Build-a-BackYard-DIY-Fire-Pit.jpg\" alt=\"Image\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Step 7: Seal and Paint (Optional)</h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Apply fire-resistant sealant if your design requires it. Finish with <strong>high-heat paint</strong> on the metal insert to protect it from corrosion.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://100things2do.ca/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/White-And-Grey-Minimalist-DIY-Home-Pinterest-Pin-3.png\" alt=\"Image\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://ak1.ostkcdn.com/images/products/is/images/direct/554257aa9ecf29c8aa5b236b70713cc13e4c9e34/Sunnydaze-Spark-Screen-40%22-Diameter-Heavy-Duty-Mesh-Steel-Fire-Pit-Accessory.jpg\" alt=\"Image\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Step 8: Add Seating Area</h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Arrange outdoor chairs or benches at least <strong>7 feet away</strong> from the fire pit to ensure safety and comfort.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://cdn.decoist.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/Outdoor-fire-put-surrounded-by-black-chairs-plants-and-dangling-lights-50536-e1620151346668.jpg\" alt=\"Image\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://images.thdstatic.com/productImages/4770889b-7029-4af3-aecc-38971ee31413/svn/plastic-adirondack-chairs-4dpthd23020-1-64_600.jpg\" alt=\"Image\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Step 9: Test the Fire Pit</h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Start with dry wood and maintain a hot fire for at least <strong>30 minutes</strong>. Proper combustion occurs between <strong>550°F and 700°F</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.realsimple.com/thmb/fNq64-fXWbkHf1xT3JmE5OeOJa4%3D/1500x0/filters%3Ano_upscale%28%29%3Amax_bytes%28150000%29%3Astrip_icc%28%29/rsp-smokeless-fire-pits-june-24-test-cuisinart-coh-800-cleanburn-24in-maura-ruane-15-f4d91efbc12c49ed81f34bc881ac29db.jpeg\" alt=\"Image\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"/images/img-834.jpg\" alt=\"Image\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">You should notice smoke reduction as secondary flames ignite near the air holes.</p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How a Smokeless Fire Pit Works</h2>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Smokeless fire pits use <strong>double-wall construction</strong> and controlled airflow to burn smoke before it escapes.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Cool air enters from the bottom</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Heated air rises between walls</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Smoke gases re-ignite at the top</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Cleaner flame, minimal smoke</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">This design works with wood, logs, pellets, or charcoal depending on the insert.</p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Tips to Reduce Smoke Even Further</h2>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Use dry, seasoned wood only</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Remove ash after each use</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Avoid overloading the pit</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Keep wood below secondary burn holes</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Stir the fire occasionally for airflow</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Safety Guidelines</h2>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Never place a fire pit under trees or overhangs</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Keep a fire extinguisher nearby</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Avoid slopes or uneven ground</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Allow the pit to cool completely before cleaning</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>Do smokeless fire pits burn wood faster?</strong><br>Yes. They burn wood more efficiently, producing more heat with less fuel.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>Do smokeless fire pits still give off heat?</strong><br>Absolutely. They provide excellent radiant heat for cooking and warmth.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>Are smokeless fire pits safer than traditional ones?</strong><br>They are generally safer due to reduced smoke and controlled combustion when used properly.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>What should go at the bottom of a DIY fire pit?</strong><br>Sand or gravel works best to protect the base and manage heat.</p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Final Thoughts</h2>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Building your own DIY smokeless fire pit is a rewarding project that enhances outdoor living while reducing smoke and improving efficiency. With the right materials, airflow design, and safety practices, you can enjoy clean fires for years to come.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">For those who prefer ready-made solutions, <strong>Vevor.Company</strong> also offers professionally engineered smokeless fire pits built for durability, safety, and performance—often at a cost lower than DIY builds.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Whether you build or buy, a smokeless fire pit turns any backyard into a welcoming gathering space.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><a href=\"https://s.vevor.com/QTZBAZ\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\">BUY NOW</a></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://s.vevor.com/QTZBAZ\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"1024\" src=\"/images/img-831.webp\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3429\" srcset=\"/images/img-831.we